episode, Lucan then allegedly attacked

00:13:32.225 --> 00:13:34.475
his wife before she managed to escape

00:13:34.715 --> 00:13:36.885
to the Plumber’s Arms pub down the road.

00:13:38.115 --> 00:13:40.785
It's generally accepted, believed, that

00:13:40.795 --> 00:13:43.465
Lucan had been expecting his estranged

00:13:43.465 --> 00:13:46.285
wife to come downstairs, not the nanny,

00:13:46.565 --> 00:13:49.265
and that she had been the intended victim.

00:13:50.025 --> 00:13:52.255
He had been planning to kill Lady

00:13:52.355 --> 00:13:54.945
Lucan, dispose of her body and

00:13:55.155 --> 00:13:57.375
take back the children and house.

00:13:58.785 --> 00:14:01.285
Now, based on what we know of Lucan’s

00:14:01.305 --> 00:14:03.675
mental state at the time, and their

00:14:03.675 --> 00:14:05.795
deteriorating marriage, this certainly

00:14:05.795 --> 00:14:08.065
seems like a plausible theory.

00:14:08.945 --> 00:14:10.495
So, what happened?

00:14:10.695 --> 00:14:11.775
What did Lord Lucan

00:14:11.945 --> 00:14:13.145
have to say about this?

00:14:13.235 --> 00:14:16.185
Did he deny it, what was his defence?

00:14:17.105 --> 00:14:18.605
Well, he said nothing.

00:14:19.475 --> 00:14:21.115
As you might have guessed from the

00:14:21.135 --> 00:14:23.605
title of this episode, Lord Lucan

00:14:23.885 --> 00:14:26.985
disappeared and was never seen again,

00:14:27.435 --> 00:14:29.645
resulting in one of the biggest murder

00:14:29.645 --> 00:14:31.725
mysteries in modern British history.

00:14:33.265 --> 00:14:35.375
We do know something of his movements

00:14:35.405 --> 00:14:37.495
immediately after the murder, however.

00:14:38.515 --> 00:14:41.375
It's thought that he drove 70 kilometres

00:14:41.635 --> 00:14:43.945
to a friend's house in a village in

00:14:43.955 --> 00:14:46.565
Sussex, close to London, but only

00:14:46.575 --> 00:14:48.895
stayed for a few hours and left

00:14:48.895 --> 00:14:50.715
in the early hours of the morning.

00:14:52.165 --> 00:14:54.875
His story, his cover, according to

00:14:54.875 --> 00:14:57.035
friends, was that he had walked in

00:14:57.035 --> 00:14:59.315
on his wife being attacked by another

00:14:59.455 --> 00:15:02.385
mystery man and that he was now hiding

00:15:02.565 --> 00:15:04.765
because his wife had accused him of

00:15:04.765 --> 00:15:07.635
hiring a hitman, a contract killer.

00:15:09.075 --> 00:15:11.965
But after that, we know very little.

00:15:12.975 --> 00:15:15.485
Three days later, on November the 10th,

00:15:15.905 --> 00:15:18.945
his bloodstained car was found abandoned

00:15:19.115 --> 00:15:21.225
– with a piece of lead piping in the

00:15:21.225 --> 00:15:23.955
boot – at the port in Newhaven, near

00:15:23.965 --> 00:15:25.915
Brighton, on the south coast of England.

00:15:27.645 --> 00:15:31.225
After that, nobody to this very day

00:15:31.535 --> 00:15:33.525
knows what happened to Lord Lucan.

00:15:34.355 --> 00:15:36.305
Well, nobody publicly

00:15:36.545 --> 00:15:37.625
knows anything about it.

00:15:38.905 --> 00:15:41.805
And, as you might imagine, this has led

00:15:41.805 --> 00:15:44.365
to a whole host of theories about what

00:15:44.365 --> 00:15:46.835
happened to him, where he went, and

00:15:47.015 --> 00:15:49.655
whether he is, in fact, still alive.

00:15:50.705 --> 00:15:52.805
In fact, over the years there have

00:15:52.835 --> 00:15:55.415
been countless - as many as 70,

00:15:55.425 --> 00:15:57.848
according to some sources - supposed

00:15:57.848 --> 00:16:00.258
‘sightings’ of Lucan around the world

00:16:00.418 --> 00:16:03.028
in places as far-flung as Australia,

00:16:03.298 --> 00:16:05.678
India, France, and Mozambique.

00:16:07.138 --> 00:16:10.248
Although in 1999 he was declared

00:16:10.448 --> 00:16:13.288
‘legally dead’ and a death certificate

00:16:13.418 --> 00:16:17.188
was officially issued in 2016, his body

00:16:17.378 --> 00:16:20.698
has never been found, so nobody can say

00:16:20.698 --> 00:16:22.988
for sure whether he’s dead or alive.

00:16:24.428 --> 00:16:26.828
The first supposed sighting came

00:16:26.828 --> 00:16:30.178
in January of 1975, in Melbourne,

00:16:30.288 --> 00:16:32.948
Australia, and he was also allegedly

00:16:32.958 --> 00:16:34.968
seen in northwest France in the

00:16:34.968 --> 00:16:36.678
year or so after the murder.

00:16:37.688 --> 00:16:39.598
People also claimed to have seen him in

00:16:39.778 --> 00:16:42.498
Mozambique and Zimbabwe, and there was

00:16:42.518 --> 00:16:45.108
even a theory that he was living in India

00:16:45.258 --> 00:16:47.978
as a beach hippy called "Jungle Barry.”

00:16:49.498 --> 00:16:52.488
Some of the other whacky theories include

00:16:52.488 --> 00:16:55.168
that Lord Lucan was held to ransom by the

00:16:55.228 --> 00:16:58.328
Irish Republican Army and, incredibly,

00:16:58.638 --> 00:17:01.348
that he had shot himself and his remains

00:17:01.478 --> 00:17:03.858
were fed to the tigers in an English

00:17:03.858 --> 00:17:05.748
zoo immediately after the murder.

00:17:07.268 --> 00:17:08.248
And there’s more.

00:17:08.618 --> 00:17:10.558
Police have investigated fingerprints

00:17:10.588 --> 00:17:12.588
on beer glasses in South Africa,

00:17:12.838 --> 00:17:14.438
and tracked money moving to

00:17:14.448 --> 00:17:16.218
bank accounts in Latin America.

00:17:16.988 --> 00:17:18.988
People have claimed to see Lucan at

00:17:18.988 --> 00:17:22.128
an ex-Nazi colony in Paraguay, living

00:17:22.128 --> 00:17:24.268
in a car in New Zealand, and even

00:17:24.278 --> 00:17:26.478
working as a waiter in California.

00:17:27.558 --> 00:17:29.338
And the mystery of Lord Lucan

00:17:29.548 --> 00:17:31.798
continues to this very day,

00:17:31.958 --> 00:17:33.868
almost 50 years after the murder.

00:17:34.998 --> 00:17:37.588
In 2022, a facial recognition

00:17:37.618 --> 00:17:40.258
specialist claimed that a photo of

00:17:40.258 --> 00:17:42.058
an elderly man living in Australia

00:17:42.268 --> 00:17:45.068
is an exact match for Lord Lucan.

00:17:45.998 --> 00:17:47.638
Could he have escaped and been

00:17:47.638 --> 00:17:49.448
living in Australia all these years?

00:17:50.768 --> 00:17:52.668
Using artificial intelligence to

00:17:52.838 --> 00:17:55.268
cross-reference photos of Lord Lucan

00:17:55.528 --> 00:17:58.468
with this old man in Australia, the

00:17:58.628 --> 00:18:00.928
specialist concluded that, and I’m

00:18:00.928 --> 00:18:03.398
quoting directly, “they produced a match.

00:18:03.498 --> 00:18:05.108
This isn’t an opinion, it’s

00:18:05.108 --> 00:18:07.048
science and mathematical fact”.

00:18:08.562 --> 00:18:10.662
Some say, however, that the most

00:18:10.672 --> 00:18:12.952
likely scenario is that he took a

00:18:12.962 --> 00:18:15.447
ferry from Newhaven just days after

00:18:15.582 --> 00:18:17.692
the murder, jumped off the boat,

00:18:17.892 --> 00:18:20.422
committing suicide, and his body was

00:18:20.432 --> 00:18:23.572
lost at sea, forever consigned to Davy

00:18:23.572 --> 00:18:25.802
Jones’ Locker, as a sailor might say.

00:18:27.002 --> 00:18:29.062
The only truth of this murder mystery,

00:18:29.202 --> 00:18:31.472
of this ‘whodunnit’, as we say in

00:18:31.472 --> 00:18:33.462
England, is that nobody knows for

00:18:33.462 --> 00:18:35.662
sure what happened to Lord Lucan.

00:18:36.452 --> 00:18:38.882
It was a real-life murder mystery,

00:18:39.052 --> 00:18:41.602
a real life game of Cluedo, complete

00:18:41.602 --> 00:18:43.592
with “lead piping”, one of the murder

00:18:43.592 --> 00:18:45.602
weapons used in the game of Cluedo.

00:18:46.307 --> 00:18:48.587
As a quick reminder, or if you didn't

00:18:48.587 --> 00:18:51.227
know, Cluedo is a popular board game

00:18:51.347 --> 00:18:53.297
where players try to solve a murder

00:18:53.297 --> 00:18:55.937
mystery by guessing the character, murder

00:18:55.937 --> 00:18:58.247
weapon and room where the crime occurred.

00:18:59.236 --> 00:19:02.016
And in fact, the parallels between

00:19:02.046 --> 00:19:04.136
the real-life case of Lord Lucan and

00:19:04.136 --> 00:19:06.096
the game of Cluedo aren’t limited

00:19:06.286 --> 00:19:08.226
to the discovery of the lead piping.

00:19:09.646 --> 00:19:12.366
Incredibly, in what seems like fiction

00:19:12.376 --> 00:19:15.366
but was in fact real life, in 2022

00:19:15.856 --> 00:19:17.976
it was reported that investigators

00:19:18.176 --> 00:19:20.146
didn’t only find the lead piping

00:19:20.276 --> 00:19:21.826
in Lucan’s car in Newhaven.

00:19:22.816 --> 00:19:24.396
According to the British press,

00:19:24.636 --> 00:19:27.326
investigators also found cards

00:19:27.456 --> 00:19:29.716
from the game of Cluedo in the car.

00:19:31.146 --> 00:19:32.646
And it gets weirder.

00:19:33.006 --> 00:19:34.816
Which cards did they find?

00:19:35.856 --> 00:19:37.646
Colonel Mustard, a lead

00:19:37.706 --> 00:19:39.256
pipe, and the hall.

00:19:40.732 --> 00:19:43.866
And why is this particularly strange?

00:19:44.436 --> 00:19:46.836
Colonel Mustard is a dashing military

00:19:46.836 --> 00:19:48.856
character with a large moustache,

00:19:49.116 --> 00:19:51.226
not too dissimilar to Lord Lucan’s

00:19:51.226 --> 00:19:53.686
own; his weapon was exactly the

00:19:53.686 --> 00:19:56.916
same; and the ‘hall’ location is the

00:19:56.926 --> 00:19:58.896
closest to the cellar in the game.

00:20:00.446 --> 00:20:03.256
In a further twist, police revealed that

00:20:03.266 --> 00:20:06.016
these three cards were also found to

00:20:06.016 --> 00:20:08.866
be missing from Lucan’s own Cluedo set.

00:20:10.186 --> 00:20:12.076
So, what does this all mean?

00:20:12.466 --> 00:20:15.496
Was it Lord Lucan taunting, or mocking,

00:20:15.636 --> 00:20:17.436
the police before making his escape?

00:20:18.176 --> 00:20:20.386
Was he framed by someone else?

00:20:20.586 --> 00:20:21.946
Or was someone trying

00:20:21.946 --> 00:20:23.766
to play a “funny” trick?

00:20:25.206 --> 00:20:27.406
It seems quite clear that the murder

00:20:27.516 --> 00:20:30.166
was committed by this man, by Lucan,

00:20:30.556 --> 00:20:32.906
and an innocent young life was taken.

00:20:33.886 --> 00:20:36.086
If he wasn’t the killer, then his

00:20:36.086 --> 00:20:38.456
disappearance is most suspicious.

00:20:39.376 --> 00:20:42.626
But as to what happened next, and to the

00:20:42.626 --> 00:20:45.336
question of what actually happened to Lord

00:20:45.356 --> 00:20:48.246
Lucan, well unless something drastically

00:20:48.246 --> 00:20:50.936
changes, then this is a mystery that

00:20:50.946 --> 00:20:53.996
will most likely forever remain unsolved.

00:20:56.236 --> 00:20:59.086
Ok then, that is it for today’s episode

00:20:59.236 --> 00:21:01.276
on the disappearance of Lord Lucan.

